{
  "texts": [
    "Overall, BGRU is a powerful and versatile deep-learning technique for sequential data modeling that has become increasingly popular recently.",
    "The RNNs are deep learning models commonly used for sequential data processing, such as text, speech, and time-series data.",
    "Unlike traditional neural networks that take fixed-size inputs and produce fixed-size outputs, RNNs are designed to operate on variable length sequences.",
    "They achieve this by including loops within the network that allow information to persist over time.",
    "This makes them particularly effective at processing inputs that have a temporal or sequential nature (Gul, 2020). 4."
  ]
}